<div id="classDescription">
CPortlet is the base class for portlet widgets.
<br/><br/>
A portlet displays a fragment of content, usually in terms of a block
on the side bars of a Web page.
<br/><br/>
To specify the content of the portlet, override the <?php echo CHtml::link('renderContent', array('/site/doc', 'view' => 'CPortlet', '#' => 'renderContent')); ?>
method, or insert the content code between the <?php echo CHtml::link('CController::beginWidget', array('/site/doc', 'view' => 'CController', '#' => 'beginWidget')); ?>
and <?php echo CHtml::link('CController::endWidget', array('/site/doc', 'view' => 'CController', '#' => 'endWidget')); ?> calls. For example,
<br/><br/>
<pre>
&lt;?php $this-&gt;beginWidget('zii.widgets.CPortlet'); ?&gt;
    ...insert content here...
&lt;?php $this-&gt;endWidget(); ?&gt;
</pre>
<br/><br/>
A portlet also has an optional <?php echo CHtml::link('title', array('/site/doc', 'view' => 'CPortlet', '#' => 'title')); ?>. One may also override <?php echo CHtml::link('renderDecoration', array('/site/doc', 'view' => 'CPortlet', '#' => 'renderDecoration')); ?>
to further customize the decorative display of a portlet (e.g. adding min/max buttons).</div>
